cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the submission and acceptance of papers in peer review journals, which involves aspects of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and computers and society (cs.CY). The analysis of time series data and the consideration of editor and author viewpoints also suggest a focus on computational methods and data analysis, further supporting these potential sub-categories.
